&lt;p&gt;BSS marks shared frequencies to allow 802.11ax access points to determine whether simultaneous use of spectrum is permissible. This technology reduces interference due to congestionï¼ˆå µå¡ï¼‰ and ensures consistent service to multiple connected devices in high-density environments.&lt;/p&gt;
